For bike commuters, finding a way to safely park your bike is not always an easy task. Most of the time, establishments will only propose car parking, in spite of the fact that the city of Austin offers the possibility to apply

for the free installation of bike corrals on the right of way/parking spot close to businesses. The process requires the requester to write an email to a specific service of the city, and include additional information about
the location and the business owner(s).
But there are two problems with this approach:
1) The first problem is that people do not want to spend the time to write the email and collect the necessary information.
2) The second one is that, in spite of the fact that the people in charge of the program are willing to help, the process is not completely straightforward.
